      {
        "id": 2835344,
        "name": "Jeremy Holmes",
        "username": "Jeremy_Holmes",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/jeremy_holmes/{size}/1146_2.png",
        "created_at": "2020-03-13T04:05:04.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Had the '13 version with lunch today. It had a fresh nose of flint and citrus, coupled with a gentle tropical fruit note. It is full and complex, with good shape and nice acid line. It is starting to drink very well, and whilst it doesn\u2019t have the out and out power and completeness of the 2015 version, it is right in the zone, right now.</p>",
